The Vice President of the United States, Kamala Harris, delivered a speech at the United States Military Academy at West Point's graduation ceremony. She congratulated the cadets of the Class of 2023 on their achievements and highlighted the challenges they faced, including the COVID-19 pandemic and global conflicts. Harris emphasized the importance of the United States' leadership in maintaining global security and prosperity. She also acknowledged the significance of the military's role in defending the country's ideals of freedom, democracy, and the rule of law. Harris encouraged the cadets to embrace innovation and technology, as well as to lead with character and resolve. She expressed confidence in their ability to serve the nation and reminded them that America relies on the strength and courage of West Point officers. The speech concluded with congratulations to the graduating class and a blessing for the United States of America.